% Debugger `:show` command (BETA1 spec section 3.3).
% With debugging mode enabled, `:show V` may be entered at any
% "Press the enter key..." prompt; the debugger prints the current
% binding of `?V` and then resumes single-stepping.
%
% Expected (abridged): two state dumps for `?- X is 3.`; at the
% first prompt `:show X` prints "*** :show: ?X = X" (unbound) and
% control returns to the same prompt? Actually the runtime advances
% one step after each prompt regardless of the command, so the second
% prompt shows X bound, after which Enter resumes to the answer.
